{% set frontend_parallel_mode = identity_frontend_parallel_mode | default("") | lower %}
{% set frontend_worktree_parallel_enabled = frontend_parallel_mode in ["worktree", "worktree_parallel", "enabled", "true"] %}
## Frontend Parallel Mode

{% if frontend_worktree_parallel_enabled %}
Experimental opt-in worktree task parallelism is enabled by
`identity.frontend_parallel_mode={{ identity_frontend_parallel_mode }}`.
Use it only after `@lead` or the operator has posted live ACP `cwd` smoke-test
evidence for this board.

Rules:
- Cap at 2 active implementation tasks unless the operator explicitly raises
  the cap for this board.
- Parallelism is per task, not per acceptance criterion. Each task gets one ACP
  executor session; that executor must follow the Ralph Loop one AC at a time.
- Before spawning work, fetch assigned tasks and clean only stale `/tmp/wt-*`
  worktrees that do not match an active task.
- For each newly started parallel task, from the main repo run
  `git worktree add /tmp/wt-$TASK_ID -b wt-$TASK_ID`, then use the
  `acp-delegation` implementation payload with `"cwd": "/tmp/wt-$TASK_ID"` and
  a unique label.
- Post `ACP_EXECUTOR_STARTED` only after the ACP spawn is accepted, then return
  `HEARTBEAT_OK`.
- Completion-woken ticks process child results only; do not spawn new work on a
  completion wake. Merge `wt-$TASK_ID` back to the main workspace, remove the
  worktree/branch after a clean merge, then run `acp-post-review`.
- On any worktree create, merge, cleanup, or ACP `cwd` uncertainty, stop
  parallelism, post one blocker with the exact failing command/output, and
  continue in sequential main-workspace mode until lead/operator re-enables it.
{% else %}
Default to one active implementation task. Do not create git worktrees,
isolated sessions, or parallel workspace branches during heartbeat work.
Those isolation paths have previously hidden state and caused stale merges.

When multiple assigned tasks are present, continue the oldest active
`in_progress` task first. If none is active, pick one eligible task and finish
it through evidence, ACP post-review, and handoff before starting another.

Only if `@lead` explicitly routes independent parallel slices may you run more
than one ACP child. In that case, use `acp-delegation` with disjoint file/AC
ownership, unique labels, and parent-owned final integration. Do not move
status or post completion evidence from child output until `acp-post-review`
passes.
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
